         <div type="edition" xml:lang="omy-Latn" rendition="class:38769 maturity:83211">
            <p>
<lb n="1"/><g type="symbol">*</g> svasti śrī śaka-varṣātīta 604 Ekādaśī śu<lb 
n="2" break="no"/>kla-pakṣa vulan· vaiśākha ḍa punta hiyaṁ nāyik di
<lb n="3"/>sāmvau maṅalap siddhayātra di saptamī śukla-pakṣa
<lb n="4"/>vulan· jyeṣṭha ḍa punta hiyaṁ marlapas· dari mināṅa
<lb n="5"/>tāmvan· mamāva yaṁ vala duA lakṣa daṅan· kośa
<lb n="6"/>duA ratus· cāra di sāmvau daṅan· jālan· sarivu
<lb n="7"/>tlu rātus· sapuluḥ duA vañakña dātaṁ di ma<gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="2"/>

[u]kh(a) (U/da/ja)(m/p)[...]<!-- n.11 Boechari -->
<lb n="8"/>sukhacitta di pañcamī śukla-pakṣa vula[n· Āṣāḍha]<!-- n.12 Boechari -->
<lb n="9"/>laghu mudita dātaṁ marvuAt· vanuA [Ini ....]<!-- n.13 Boechari -->
<lb n="10"/>śrīvijaya jaya siddhayātra subhikṣa n[ityakāla]<!-- n.13 Boechari -->
<!--
<g ref="sym:spiral-right" type="symbol">*</g> 
<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> siddha 
<g ref="sym:bullet-middle-hollow" type="punctuation">.</g> 
<g ref="sym:doubleBar-hooked" type="punctuation">.</g> 
<g ref="sym:floret" type="symbol">*</g> 
<g ref="sym:bullet-triple" type="punctuation">.</g>
<g ref="sym:flourish-taperOut" type="symbol">*</g>
-->
</p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
               <listApp>
		    <app loc="7">
                     <lem source="bib:Poerbatjaraka1952_01 bib:Boechari1986_01">kośa</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Coedes1930_01">ko<gap reason="undefined" unit="character" quantity="1"/></rdg>
			<note>Boechari adopts the reading kośa from </note>
                  </app>
                  <app loc="7">
                     <lem source="bib:Boechari1986_01">sapuluḥ</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Coedes1930_01 bib:Poerbatjaraka1952_01">sapulu</rdg>
                  </app>
		   <app loc="7">
			<lem>ma<gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="2"/></lem>
			<rdg source="bib:Coedes1930_01">mata jap·</rdg>
			<rdg source="bib:Poerbatjaraka1952_01">mata yap·</rdg>
			<note>Krom (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Krom1938_01"/><citedRange unit="page">25-26</citedRange></bibl>, with plate) proposed to read <foreign>malay<supplied reason="lost">u</supplied></foreign>. Although subserquent scholars have favored different readings (), to our mind Krom's proposal still deserves consideration.</note>
		   </app> 
		   <app loc="10">
                     <lem source="bib:Boechari1986_01">śrīvijaya jaya siddhayātra</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Coedes1930_01">śrīvijaya siddhayātra</rdg>
			<note>The omission of jaya was first pointed out by Poerbatjaraka.</note>
                  </app>
                     <!-- 
Notes
2. ḍa punta: CHECK does Coedes read dapunta everywhere?
2. It seems highly doubtful to me that there ever was the word di, read by Cœdès etc., at the end of this line.
7. On the reading of the end of this line, see ... Krom (1938: 421–422) who proposes malayu. See the subsequent comments of Boechari. But see also De Casparis 1982: 5.
9. Only vanuA is visible, and the lacuna starts immediately thereafter, so that theoretically the Cœdès/Boechari reading vanuĀ might still be possible.
10. -jaya jaya: see BEFEO 1930 correction XXXX. See also De Casparis 1982: 3.
                     -->
               </listApp>
